     fhir:div [ fhir:v "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"><p class=\"res-header-id\"><b>Generated Narrative: CodeSystem map-target-list-mode</b></p><a name=\"map-target-list-mode\"> </a><a name=\"hcmap-target-list-mode\"> </a><p>This case-sensitive code system <code>http://hl7.org/fhir/map-target-list-mode</code> defines the following codes:</p><table class=\"codes\"><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\"><b>Code</b></td><td><b>Display</b></td><td><b>Definition</b></td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">first<a name=\"map-target-list-mode-first\"> </a></td><td>First</td><td>when the target list is being assembled, the items for this rule go first. If more than one rule defines a first item (for a given instance of mapping) then this is an error.</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">share<a name=\"map-target-list-mode-share\"> </a></td><td>Share</td><td>the target instance is shared with the target instances generated by another rule (up to the first common n items, then create new ones).</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">last<a name=\"map-target-list-mode-last\"> </a></td><td>Last</td><td>when the target list is being assembled, the items for this rule go last. If more than one rule defines a last item (for a given instance of mapping) then this is an error.</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">single<a name=\"map-target-list-mode-single\"> </a></td><td>single</td><td>the target instance is shared with a number of target instances generated by another rule (up to the first common n items, then create new ones).</td></tr></table></div>"^^rdf:XMLLiteral ]
